QUICK SETUP CHECKLIST:
□ 1. Create GitHub repository named "drone-controller-docs"
□ 2. Create all directories listed above
□ 3. Upload the provided files (index.html, style.css, main.js, README.md)
□ 4. Add favicon.ico and logo.png to assets/images/
□ 5. Create remaining HTML files using the provided templates as guides
□ 6. Enable GitHub Pages in repository settings
□ 7. Update all "yourusername" placeholders with your GitHub username
□ 8. Test the site locally before pushing
□ 9. Commit and push all files to GitHub
□ 10. Verify site is accessible at https://yourusername.github.io/drone-controller-docs

TEMPLATE FOR MISSING PAGES:
Use the structure from the provided files (index.html, wearer-hud/index.html, etc.) as templates.
Each page should include:
- Same navigation structure
- Proper <title> tags
- Links to CSS and JS files
- Footer with relevant links
- Content appropriate to the page topic

CUSTOMIZATION NOTES:
- Replace "yourusername" with your actual GitHub username in all files
- Add your own logo and favicon in assets/images/
- Customize colors in CSS variables if desired
- Add screenshots of your actual interfaces
- Update contact information in contact/index.html

MAINTENANCE:
- Update "last-updated" spans regularly
- Keep version numbers current
- Add new pages as system features expand
- Monitor and fix any broken links
- Update screenshots when interface changes

This structure provides a comprehensive documentation system that can grow with your project!
